title: New Zealand Gross Fixed Capital Formation
description: Gross Fixed Capital Formation in New Zealand decreased to 16989 NZD Million in the second quarter of 2022 from 17574 NZD Million in the first quarter of 2022. Gross Fixed Capital Formation in New Zealand averaged 9700.07 NZD Million from 1987 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 17600 NZD Million in the fourth quarter of 2021 and a record low of 4037 NZD Million in the second quarter of 1991. This page provides the latest reported value for - New Zealand Gross Fixed Capital Formation - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: Statistics New Zealand
